        .4u class="12u$(medium)"
          h3 Like Linux ..
          p  We use <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J7YNAUYwcQw&list=PLcF9BigzPGr0Cmfe_rT1qyNlQtM5ekUtn&index=6">Creative Commons</a> to collaborate on collateral for coaching and training – toolkits, not frameworks – for <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/exponential-business-agility-xscale-practice-pattern-language-merel/" target="_blank">Descaling Business Agility</a>, &nbsp;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/exponential-product-management-xscale-language-peter-merel/" target="_blank">3D Product Management</a> and&nbsp; <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/xdevops-xscale-pattern-language-peter-merel/" target="_blank">XDevOps</a>.
          p The opposite of the Agile Industrial Complex, we're coaches, not trainers, using XSCALE internally to collaborate on client engagements, presentation collateral, patterns and tools.
          div style="text-align:center"
            ul.actions
              li
                a.button.special href="#signatory"Join the XSCALE Alliance

        div class=("4u$ 12u$(medium)")
          h3 For Descaling Organizations.
          p We don't prescribe XSCALE as a framework nor make clients dependent on XSCALE coaches or partners. We build slender but uncompromising new capabilities that self-propagate - that grow exponentially while proving outcomes, lowering resistance, and reducing risk as they grow.
          p Self-directing portfolios of self-managing streams of self-organizing teams of the client's own staff through <a href="#transformation">self-propagating transformation</a>. It's quicker, better, cheaper and, yes, safer too.
